  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Finding the meeting time of two cyclist  after starting at different times and going in the same direction</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>A cyclist starts from a point travelling at a constant speed of {@v1@} km/h.
Another cyclist starts from the same point, {@delay_h@} hours later, travelling in the same direction at a constant speed of {@v2@} km/h.</p>
<p>How long after the second cyclist starts will the second cyclist catch up with the first?</p>
<p> Time \(=\) [[input:ans1]] hours  [[validation:ans1]]  [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>The first cyclist starts earlier, so the distance they cover before the second cyclist starts is given by its velocity multiplied by the time difference:<br>
 \({@v1@} \times {@delay_h@} = {@head_start@} \text{ km}.\)</p>

<p>Since both cyclists travel in the same direction, the relative speed is:<br> \({@v2@} - {@v1@} = {@rel_speed@} \text{ km/h}.\)</p>
<p>Therefore, time taken to catch up is:<br> \(\frac{{@head_start@}}{{@rel_speed@}} = {@ta@} \text{ hours}.\)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
